The paper deals with the online weighted bipartite matching problem, which is a fundamental problem in the online algorithms literature. The paper presents a randomized algorithm that achieves a competitive ratio of at least 0.501, breaking the long-standing 1/2 barrier. This suggests that the problem is strictly easier than submodular welfare maximization in the online setting. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also relies on a controlled use of randomness, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
